  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technology Sales Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Prospecting:</strong> Identifying new business opportunities, generating leads, and conducting outreach (cold calling/emailing).</li><li><strong>Consultative Selling:</strong> Analyzing client requirements to recommend tailored technical solutions.</li><li><strong>Demonstrations:</strong> Performing product demos, proof of concepts (POCs), and technical presentations.</li><li><strong>Relationship Management:</strong> Building rapport with existing clients to drive retention and upselling.</li><li><strong>Contract Negotiation:</strong> Negotiating prices, service renewals, warranties, and closing deals.</li><li><strong>Market Intelligence:</strong> Monitoring competitor activity and industry trends. </li></ul><p><strong>Common Qualifications & Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Business, IT, Engineering, or relevant field.</li><li>Proven experience in B2B sales or technical roles.</li><li>Strong knowledge of SaaS, cloud computing, or specific industry tech (e.g., AI, cybersecurity).</li><li>Excellent negotiation, interpersonal, and presentation skills.</li><li>Proficiency in CRM software (e.g., Salesforce, HubSpot). </li></ul>",
